<th class="summary" colspan="2" style="background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;">First Crusade</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;">Part of the <a href="/wiki/Crusades" title="Crusades">Crusades</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align: center; font-size: 90%; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa; line-height: 1.5em;"><a href="/wiki/File:1099jerusalem.jpg" class="image" title="1099jerusalem.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/1099jerusalem.jpg/300px-1099jerusalem.jpg" width="300" height="287" border="0" /></a><br />
The <a href="/wiki/Siege_of_Jerusalem_(1099)" title="Siege of Jerusalem (1099)">capture of Jerusalem</a> marked the First Crusade's success</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2">
<table class="infobox" width="100%" style="margin: 0; cellpadding: 0; padding: 0; border: 0;">
<tr>
<th style="padding-right: 1em;">Date</th>
<td>1096–1099</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding-right: 1em;">Location</th>
<td><span class="location"><a href="/wiki/Near_East" title="Near East">Near East</a> (<a href="/wiki/Anatolia" title="Anatolia">Anatolia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Levant" title="Levant">Levant</a>, <a href="/wiki/Palestine" title="Palestine">Palestine</a>)</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding-right: 1em;">Result</th>
<td>Decisive <a href="/wiki/Christian" title="Christian">Christian</a> victory and <a href="/wiki/Crusader_states" title="Crusader states">land control</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding-right: 1em;">Territorial<br />
changes</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Anatolia" title="Anatolia">Anatolia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Levant" title="Levant">Levant</a> captured for <a href="/wiki/Christendom" title="Christendom">Christendom</a>;<br />
<a href="/wiki/Kingdom_of_Jerusalem" title="Kingdom of Jerusalem">Kingdom of Jerusalem</a>/<a href="/wiki/Crusader_states" title="Crusader states">crusader states</a> created</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
